WEBVTT

00:02.100 --> 00:02.433
- Previously,

00:02.433 --> 00:02.700
- Previously,
on "Below Deck"...

00:04.700 --> 00:06.000
- Ow. F---.
I need help. I need help.

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
The nerve was pinched.

00:08.000 --> 00:09.400
I'm pissed off. I'm grumpy.

00:09.400 --> 00:11.166
I have no control
over anything right now.

00:11.166 --> 00:14.033
Now it's EJ's deck.

00:14.033 --> 00:16.033
- Mmm. With cheese.

00:16.033 --> 00:18.033
- Bruno takes
a lot of pressure off me,

00:18.033 --> 00:19.166
because I can just take care
of the main courses.

00:19.166 --> 00:20.700
- Easy J, I wanted to ask

00:20.700 --> 00:22.300
if you wanted to go out
to dinner with me.

00:22.300 --> 00:23.433
- A true gentleman
takes the time

00:23.433 --> 00:25.166
to make the right move.

00:25.166 --> 00:26.567
We're doing it big time, girl.
- [chuckles]

00:26.567 --> 00:28.300
- Crazy news.

00:28.300 --> 00:30.533
Pretty much when the charter
ends, I'm out of here.

00:30.533 --> 00:33.000
- That sh-- over there.
- It's breaking hard.

00:33.000 --> 00:35.033
Due to safety reasons, we won't
be leaving the dock today.

00:35.033 --> 00:36.266
- What?
- Well, that sucks...

00:38.333 --> 00:41.467
- I have never spent the whole
entire charter on the dock.

00:41.467 --> 00:44.600
Whatever we can do to put
this thing right over the top.

00:44.600 --> 00:47.066
Y'all need to get
your butts in the seats.

00:47.066 --> 00:49.000
[all cheer]

00:52.333 --> 00:54.166
- Can we lounge
when we finish everything?

00:54.166 --> 00:56.200
- Last I checked,
Kate was my boss, not you.

00:56.200 --> 00:58.200
- I am going to go to bed.
- Can I eat dinner?

00:58.200 --> 00:59.600
- You got a two-hour break.
I didn't get a break.

00:59.600 --> 01:01.066
You are gonna stay up
and help Bri.

01:01.066 --> 01:04.300
- This is, like, sadistic sh--.

01:04.300 --> 01:05.600
♪ ♪

01:05.600 --> 01:07.033
[foghorn blares]

01:07.033 --> 01:10.066
[upbeat music]

01:10.066 --> 01:17.133
♪ ♪

01:21.734 --> 01:24.367
[hip-hop music]

01:24.367 --> 01:26.600
- Do you wanna wash or dry?

01:26.600 --> 01:29.233
- I'll dry.
- Okay.

01:29.233 --> 01:32.767
- Kate, I just wanna strangle
her, but I'm good person,

01:32.767 --> 01:36.100
and I'm trying
to suppress that feeling.

01:36.100 --> 01:38.066
- Good night.
- Thank you. [smooches]

01:38.066 --> 01:40.233
♪ ♪

01:40.233 --> 01:42.500
- I'm gonna pee very quickly.

01:42.500 --> 01:45.200
♪ ♪

01:45.200 --> 01:47.333
- Hi.

01:47.333 --> 01:49.100
- How was your night?
- Fine.

01:58.667 --> 02:01.600
It's definitely more difficult
working wi

02:01.633 --> 02:03.266
who sincerely believes

02:03.300 --> 02:04.533
they're working
extremely hard,

02:04.567 --> 02:06.333
and they're not.

02:06.367 --> 02:07.767
She just needs to suck it up
and do the job.

02:08.000 --> 02:11.100
So I gotta make sure
she goes to bed.

02:11.133 --> 02:16.100
♪ ♪

02:16.133 --> 02:18.066
- I'm having a brain fart.
Where do we keep these?

02:18.100 --> 02:21.000
Up here, right?

02:21.033 --> 02:23.066
They don't, like,
go all the way down in there.

02:23.100 --> 02:26.000
- That's okay.
- Okay. I'm losing my mind.

02:26.033 --> 02:28.633
- Jen, she's so tired,
she's delirious,

02:28.667 --> 02:31.133
and she's not
helping me at all.

02:31.133 --> 02:33.066
- Just need to
lay my head down...

02:33.100 --> 02:34.600
- Go to bed.
- I'm done.

02:34.633 --> 02:36.600
- All right, thank you.
- Thank you.

02:36.633 --> 02:43.667
♪ ♪

02:45.200 --> 02:48.000
- Well, Baker, gonna miss ya.

02:48.033 --> 02:50.433
- Miss you too, booboo.
- Who knows?

02:50.433 --> 02:52.667
Maybe you guys will get
someone to replace me.

02:52.700 --> 02:54.433
- Yeah, right?
- I will miss

02:54.467 --> 02:56.500
90% of the people of "Valor."

02:56.533 --> 02:59.000
Some of them,
I could probably go without,

02:59.033 --> 03:02.400
but there is a couple
real cool ones onboard.

03:02.433 --> 03:05.100
Oh!
Sometimes, moments like this

03:05.133 --> 03:07.633
you just gotta enjoy.
- [chuckles] Right?

03:07.667 --> 03:10.500
- It just doesn't feel like
I'm leaving tomorrow.

03:10.533 --> 03:12.133
- Yeah.
- It never does.

03:12.166 --> 03:14.233
- You can still make
the most of it.

03:14.266 --> 03:17.166
[chuckles]

03:17.200 --> 03:18.700
- Well, Baker...

03:18.734 --> 03:21.033
- Eej.

03:21.033 --> 03:23.266
- This is it.

03:23.300 --> 03:27.066
I wonder when the next time
I'll be here in Saint Martin.

03:27.066 --> 03:30.700
- Saint Martins.

03:30.734 --> 03:32.667
- Time flies
when you're having fun.

03:32.700 --> 03:34.433
- Mm-hmm.

03:34.467 --> 03:39.200
♪ ♪

03:39.233 --> 03:42.266
- [grunting, moans]

03:43.734 --> 03:45.667
So, uh...

03:45.700 --> 03:48.166
- What time is it?
- Time to freaking

03:48.200 --> 03:50.066
get this sh-- done
and go to bed.

03:50.100 --> 03:52.033
- Shall we?

03:52.066 --> 03:53.166
Oh, well.

03:53.200 --> 03:56.166
[playful dynamic music]

03:56.200 --> 04:02.233
♪ ♪

04:04.333 --> 04:05.700
[electronic music]

04:05.734 --> 04:08.734
[alarm clocking buzzing]

04:08.767 --> 04:15.367
♪ ♪

04:15.400 --> 04:17.433
- Apple turnovers?
Those are new.

04:17.467 --> 04:19.000
- Yeah.

04:20.633 --> 04:22.200
- Your arm feels better?

04:25.467 --> 04:27.233
- Attention all crew:
now that the conditions

04:27.233 --> 04:29.100
have settled down a little bit,
I think it's safe

04:29.133 --> 04:31.233
to take the guests out
for a little morning cruise.

04:31.233 --> 04:33.266
[machine buzzes]

04:34.266 --> 04:37.600
- Having such a negative season
just doesn't sit well with me.

04:37.633 --> 04:40.100
- Baker.
- Niki-Niki.

04:40.100 --> 04:42.066
- Sitting in my room
put things in perspective,

04:42.100 --> 04:44.467
and now I'm gonna come out
with a fire under my ass,

04:44.500 --> 04:47.700
and I'm gonna actually be a
team player and do a good job.

04:47.734 --> 04:50.066
- I think we might be
leaving the dock today.

04:50.100 --> 04:53.233
- Oh, my God, is it happening?
- It might be happening.

04:53.266 --> 04:54.633
- Hey, Nico.

04:54.667 --> 04:56.266
Should you be
wearing your sling?

04:56.266 --> 04:58.233
- I think it's
a bit dramatic, but...

04:58.266 --> 04:59.467
- Don't be too cool
for a sling, Nico.

04:59.500 --> 05:01.133
- I'm not too cool for a sling.

05:01.133 --> 05:04.467
[soft, slow music]

05:04.500 --> 05:06.233
- [groans]

05:06.266 --> 05:08.100
- Come on, Jen.

05:08.133 --> 05:10.600
♪ ♪

05:10.633 --> 05:12.266
- [sighs] F---.

05:12.300 --> 05:14.200
- Do we have any news
on the day?

05:14.233 --> 05:15.500
- It's looking good.

05:15.533 --> 05:18.467
- What time is it?
- 9:03.

05:18.500 --> 05:21.633
- Uh-oh, Jen's late.
Tick-tock, Jen.

05:21.667 --> 05:25.233
♪ The longer you are late,
the more you will pay for it ♪

05:25.266 --> 05:28.533
Hello. It's 9:07.
- Good morning.

05:28.567 --> 05:30.166
Yeah, I don't feel good,
so I'm here.

05:30.166 --> 05:32.033
- Oh, none of us feel good.

05:32.033 --> 05:35.300
Did you sleep all right?

05:35.300 --> 05:36.700
Jen?

05:36.700 --> 05:37.700
- I'm just on
the verge of tears.

05:37.734 --> 05:39.433
I don't feel good.

05:39.433 --> 05:41.166
- Oh, why are you on
the verge of tears?

05:41.166 --> 05:43.100
Why don't you--
- Because I don't feel good.

05:43.133 --> 05:45.300
- I can handle this if you feel
really, really sick.

05:45.300 --> 05:47.166
- It's okay.

05:47.200 --> 05:48.767
- Jen tells me her problems;
I give her solutions.

05:49.000 --> 05:50.500
Then she finds problems
in those solutions,

05:50.533 --> 05:52.166
which become new problems.

05:52.166 --> 05:55.633
How do you solve
a problem like Jen?

05:55.667 --> 05:57.300
- [clears throat]

05:57.300 --> 05:58.633
- We're gonna
have to move quick.

05:58.667 --> 06:01.667
Let's go, let's go.

06:01.700 --> 06:04.700
- What's that sound?
- Engines! Whoo!

06:04.700 --> 06:06.500
- That's a good sound.

06:06.533 --> 06:08.400
- It's good to have
Nico back on deck,

06:08.433 --> 06:10.300
because we still need him.

06:10.333 --> 06:13.133
- 75 feet astern
to the breakwater.

06:13.166 --> 06:15.333
- Buddy!
- Pay attention here, huh?

06:15.333 --> 06:19.000
- [yelling indistinctly]

06:19.033 --> 06:20.433
- Yes.
- We made it.

06:20.467 --> 06:22.433
- We made it.

06:22.467 --> 06:25.000
- Once around the park,
and we're headed back.

06:25.033 --> 06:26.467
- A morning cruise?

06:26.467 --> 06:28.667
- That's it.
That's all we're gonna do.

06:28.700 --> 06:30.467
I'm only doing it
for the money.

06:30.500 --> 06:31.600
- Morning, Nico.

06:33.333 --> 06:35.166
- Feels a lot better.

06:35.200 --> 06:36.467
I realized that I have
been a dick to EJ,

06:36.467 --> 06:38.333
but at the same time,

06:38.333 --> 06:40.066
I'm still dealing with
a lot of things in my head,

06:40.066 --> 06:42.066
especially with
the death of my brother.

06:42.066 --> 06:44.433
I haven't been in
the right frame of mind,

06:44.467 --> 06:47.600
and since EJ's come onboard,
it's hard to admit,

06:47.633 --> 06:50.400
but the deck team's
come a long way.

06:50.433 --> 06:52.033
I need to respect that.

06:52.066 --> 06:53.633
- Yeah, it's good
to have you back.

06:53.633 --> 06:55.367
- This is a pretty part
of the island.

06:55.400 --> 06:57.200
- And the water is gorg'.

06:57.233 --> 06:59.066
- And I've got the bacon.

06:59.100 --> 07:01.333
- Ooh, nice and crispy. Yes!

07:01.367 --> 07:03.767
- What's the breakfast
special today, Jen?

07:04.000 --> 07:05.767
- I have not been informed
of that information,

07:05.767 --> 07:07.633
but I will find out.
I'll be right back.

07:07.633 --> 07:09.500
- Are they keeping it
a secret from you?

07:09.500 --> 07:11.633
- I think Kate knows,
and Matt know,

07:11.633 --> 07:14.300
but they don't like to share
things with me sometimes.

07:14.333 --> 07:16.633
- We just wanna make sure
we save room for it.

07:16.667 --> 07:18.500
- Surprise,
the breakfast special is--

07:18.500 --> 07:20.367
I don't know
what the f---ing special is,

07:20.400 --> 07:23.100
'cause my chief stew won't
f---ing communicate to me.

07:23.100 --> 07:26.467
They're requesting that
we inform them of the special,

07:26.500 --> 07:27.767
which nobody's
informed me of yet,

07:28.000 --> 07:29.600
so if you'd like to tell me

07:29.633 --> 07:31.433
what the breakfast special is,
I can let them know.

07:31.467 --> 07:33.367
- That was the most
complicated, long-winded way

07:33.367 --> 07:34.734
of asking Matt what the f---
the breakfast special was.

07:35.000 --> 07:36.600
- Yeah? What was it?
- Eggs Benedict.

07:36.633 --> 07:38.200
- Okay.

07:38.233 --> 07:41.266
[electronic music]

07:41.266 --> 07:42.667
- These are ready to go?
- Yes, they are.

07:42.667 --> 07:45.133
Thank you very much.

07:45.133 --> 07:47.066
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

07:47.100 --> 07:48.266
- You know, I love
a challenge. I really do.

07:48.266 --> 07:50.133
And these charter guests,

07:50.166 --> 07:52.734
they're challenging me
to every extent possible.

07:52.767 --> 07:54.533
But I'm just tired
of seeing their face.

07:54.533 --> 07:56.266
These people can leave.

07:56.300 --> 07:58.633
- Fancy!
- Bon appétit.

08:00.400 --> 08:02.400
- You don't like it?

08:02.400 --> 08:03.533
Ah...

08:03.567 --> 08:04.633
♪ ♪

08:08.567 --> 08:10.500
- Nico-meister...

08:10.533 --> 08:12.400
you wanna kinda help start
getting ready up on the bow?

08:12.433 --> 08:14.400
- Okay, no worries.

08:14.400 --> 08:16.400
- Oh, my God,
we're turning around already.

08:16.400 --> 08:18.166
- We are headed back
to the marina.

08:18.166 --> 08:20.567
- No, that's it.
- This sucks.

08:22.300 --> 08:23.667
- Deck crew, on your toes.

08:23.700 --> 08:25.667
- Bruno, EJ,
You ready up on the bow?

08:25.700 --> 08:27.300
- Yep.
- In the bow. Standby.

08:27.300 --> 08:28.767
- Copy.
- All right, I'm headed in.

08:29.000 --> 08:31.433
♪ ♪

08:31.433 --> 08:33.367
- So, your line's
gonna go on first.

08:33.400 --> 08:36.033
I really didn't wanna throw
this f---ing line either.

08:36.066 --> 08:39.400
- Use your left arm.
- Chuck it to him up forward.

08:39.433 --> 08:41.266
- Let's get that line on
in a hurry.

08:41.300 --> 08:43.133
- Baker, let me know
when it's on the cleat.

08:43.166 --> 08:44.667
- All right.
- The deck team's

08:44.700 --> 08:46.300
definitely in a better place
than when I came.

08:46.300 --> 08:47.433
- If you're gonna
throw that thing,

08:47.467 --> 08:48.700
get it to the goddamn dock.

08:48.734 --> 08:51.033
- Watch the bow!
- God damn it!

08:51.033 --> 08:52.400
- They're proficient.
They got it.

08:52.433 --> 08:54.266
How tight am I looking there?

08:54.300 --> 08:56.033
- You're probably gonna need
to give a little...

08:56.066 --> 08:57.500
- Pull, pull, pull, pull,
pull, pull, pull, pull.

08:57.533 --> 08:59.600
- How tight's our bow?
- It's tight.

08:59.600 --> 09:01.433
- Lock it off.

09:01.467 --> 09:02.600
Nice job, guys.

09:02.633 --> 09:04.333
♪ ♪

09:04.333 --> 09:05.333
- Oh, f---.

09:05.333 --> 09:07.266
♪ ♪

09:07.300 --> 09:09.266
- That's so great,
they did our laundry.

09:09.300 --> 09:11.133
- This is over-packing
to the limit.

09:12.734 --> 09:14.734
- See you soon, Bruno.

09:14.767 --> 09:19.600
- Everybody on the main deck
aft in 15 minutes.

09:19.633 --> 09:22.467
- [sighs]
I just wish I could, like,

09:22.467 --> 09:25.433
eat and rest like a proper
sick person should.

09:25.467 --> 09:29.033
♪ ♪

09:29.066 --> 09:30.166
- They're about
to lay it on us.

09:30.200 --> 09:32.700
♪ ♪

09:32.734 --> 09:34.667
- Take care. Safe travels.

09:34.700 --> 09:37.600
- Thank you for everything.
- Hope you had a good time.

09:37.633 --> 09:39.600
- I had so much fun.
- Thank you. Thanks. Thank you.

09:39.600 --> 09:41.500
- Have a great trip home.
- Thank you.

09:41.500 --> 09:43.700
- Ah, you're welcome.
- The best--the best job.

09:43.734 --> 09:45.367
You know,
this was really, really great,

09:45.367 --> 09:46.767
and we had a good time,

09:46.767 --> 09:49.433
but there was
a disappointment for us.

09:49.467 --> 09:52.033
For Michela and Jason,

09:52.066 --> 09:53.500
this was such
a big deal to them,

09:53.533 --> 09:56.200
but it's been kind of
a downer for them.

09:56.233 --> 09:58.033
I don't even know
where they are,

09:58.066 --> 10:00.233
and I think
they might have left.

10:03.633 --> 10:04.166
- For Michela and Jason,

10:06.100 --> 10:08.233
it's been kind of
a downer for them.

10:08.233 --> 10:10.033
I don't even know
where they are,

10:10.066 --> 10:11.767
and I think
they might have left.

10:12.000 --> 10:15.166
And then, the crew's great,
but if it were my restaurant,

10:15.200 --> 10:18.100
a lot of things would
have been sent back.

10:18.100 --> 10:19.133
- What?

10:22.233 --> 10:24.266
- You don't like it?

10:24.300 --> 10:25.767
Ah...

10:26.000 --> 10:27.667
- This woman waits
till the last minute

10:27.667 --> 10:31.200
to destroy my food in front of
the crew and Captain Lee?

10:31.233 --> 10:34.000
Talk about class.
I bet you her restaurant sucks.

10:34.000 --> 10:35.600
- I just know you could have
taken it to another level,

10:35.633 --> 10:37.367
and I just felt
that level was missed.

10:37.400 --> 10:39.467
I have to share that,
but thank you so much.

10:39.500 --> 10:41.266
- I've never seen
a primary charter guest

10:41.266 --> 10:42.767
just leave the boat,

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
so this is kind of
uncharted territory.

10:45.000 --> 10:47.133
- Bye, guys.
- Hey.

10:47.166 --> 10:49.767
- That was interesting.
- They just left?

10:50.000 --> 10:52.100
- She's awesome.

10:52.133 --> 10:53.533
- Let's go to work.

10:53.567 --> 10:56.533
[hip-hop music]

10:56.567 --> 10:59.233
♪ ♪

10:59.266 --> 11:01.000
I need everybody
in the crew mess.

11:01.033 --> 11:02.000
- Roger.

11:02.033 --> 11:07.033
♪ ♪

11:07.033 --> 11:09.166
- Okay.
All in all, with, you know,

11:09.200 --> 11:11.000
not being able to
get off the dock,

11:11.033 --> 11:13.266
I thought it went pretty well.

11:13.300 --> 11:16.266
The one girl, you know, kind of
surprised me a little bit

11:16.300 --> 11:19.166
with her assessment of things,
but I don't see

11:19.166 --> 11:23.133
where we could have done
a lot differently than we did.

11:23.166 --> 11:25.166
Matt, was there some food
issues that I wasn't aware of?

11:25.200 --> 11:26.700
- I think she is someone

11:26.734 --> 11:29.266
that will always
have something to say.

11:29.300 --> 11:32.133
- One thing I hate
to do is babysit,

11:32.166 --> 11:34.367
but I do have concerns
about the galley,

11:34.400 --> 11:37.533
and so it seems like
I'm gonna have to watch Matt

11:37.567 --> 11:40.567
more closely than
I normally would.

11:40.600 --> 11:44.367
We did $15,000.

11:44.400 --> 11:47.400
That's 1,363 apiece.

11:47.433 --> 11:51.333
Oh, by the way,
EJ will be leaving us today.

11:51.333 --> 11:52.667
- What?
- Last day.

11:52.700 --> 11:54.266
He's got to get back
to his other boat.

11:54.300 --> 11:56.066
Thanks for helping us out.
I appreciate it.

11:56.066 --> 11:57.467
- It was my pleasure.

11:57.467 --> 12:00.467
- Captain,
can you say that again?

12:00.467 --> 12:05.300
Oh, I'm gonna miss
you so much. Bye!

12:05.333 --> 12:07.533
- And maybe we'll get to work
together soon sometime.

12:07.567 --> 12:09.533
- I sure hope so.

12:09.567 --> 12:11.533
- EJ did everything I asked him
to do, and did it well.

12:11.567 --> 12:13.734
I don't think I could have
asked for a better performance.

12:13.734 --> 12:17.133
Nico's gonna have to step up,
with EJ being gone.

12:17.166 --> 12:18.433
- Well, I appreciate
you hanging out.

12:18.467 --> 12:20.033
- Yeah.
- Yeah, definitely.

12:20.066 --> 12:21.533
- You did a great job.
- It was fun.

12:21.567 --> 12:23.200
- Thanks, guys.
I appreciate it a lot.

12:23.233 --> 12:24.700
- Ya, mon.
- [chuckles]

12:24.734 --> 12:27.767
- So, my wife, Mary Anne,
is coming in today.

12:28.000 --> 12:29.467
- Yay.
- Oh, cool.

12:29.500 --> 12:31.066
- It's very rare that my wife

12:31.100 --> 12:33.200
ever gets to join me
on charter.

12:33.233 --> 12:34.700
I'm excited about it,

12:34.734 --> 12:36.367
but I've had enough
to worry about.

12:36.400 --> 12:38.500
Mary Anne and I might
join you guys for dinner.

12:38.533 --> 12:41.233
- Yay, that's exciting.
- Kate found Jesus.

12:41.266 --> 12:43.200
Bri found all the guys
on the boat.

12:43.233 --> 12:45.500
You know, Captain Lee,
his wife's coming along.

12:45.500 --> 12:49.367
Everybody's getting a little
loving, except for yours truly.

12:49.367 --> 12:50.767
This kind of sucks.

12:50.767 --> 12:52.500
- Let's go to work, guys.
- Thank you.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.233
- Thank you, Cap.
- Thank you.

12:54.233 --> 12:57.166
[electronic music]

12:57.200 --> 12:59.166
♪ ♪

12:59.200 --> 13:01.633
- Ow! F---er.

13:01.667 --> 13:03.367
- Did you hit your head?
- Oh!

13:03.367 --> 13:06.367
It always gets you
on the way out, don't it?

13:06.400 --> 13:08.166
- I can't believe
you're leaving, EJ.

13:08.200 --> 13:10.133
- I know, Eej.
- That's so sad.

13:10.133 --> 13:11.500
- I know.
- Easy J, come and go,

13:11.533 --> 13:13.467
turning and burning.

13:13.500 --> 13:15.000
I'm bummed out nothing
really got off the ground

13:15.000 --> 13:17.000
with EJ and myself,

13:17.033 --> 13:18.533
but I'm sure I'll see him
after this charter season,

13:18.533 --> 13:20.400
and every time I say,
"Roger Dodger,"

13:20.433 --> 13:22.200
I'll think of him.
- We were hoping

13:22.233 --> 13:24.200
the ship was gonna be delayed,
but it wasn't.

13:24.233 --> 13:26.767
- When was the last time
you saw this?

13:27.000 --> 13:28.667
- [laughs] I know.

13:28.700 --> 13:31.000
- Thank God
that f---ing guy is leaving.

13:31.033 --> 13:32.734
I know Baker
likes him and all...

13:32.767 --> 13:34.400
- I know.

13:34.400 --> 13:36.266
- [gasps] Sh--, man. It's real.
- I know.

13:36.300 --> 13:37.667
- Before he came,
everything was good,

13:37.700 --> 13:39.367
so I'm gonna
make it good again.

13:39.400 --> 13:41.133
I'm so happy
that EJ's leaving.

13:41.133 --> 13:42.667
I just wanna boot him
back to Canada.

13:42.700 --> 13:45.500
- I'll be seeing you soon.
- You're welcome.

13:45.533 --> 13:47.533
- I'm ready to
take charge once again,

13:47.533 --> 13:49.667
and actually have a good time
on deck and have some fun.

13:49.667 --> 13:51.500
Like, bye, EJ!

13:51.533 --> 13:53.500
No, I'm not gonna
add you on Facebook."

13:53.533 --> 13:56.166
- Easy-J!

13:56.200 --> 13:59.133
- My girl. My girl.
- My crew boo.

13:59.166 --> 14:00.567
I'll miss you.

14:00.600 --> 14:02.266
- You off, EJ?
- Yeah.

14:02.300 --> 14:04.166
Time to get out
of here, brother man.

14:04.166 --> 14:05.667
You guys need to reconnect
when you're in Lauderdale.

14:05.700 --> 14:07.266
- Oh, yeah.
- Yeah, I told her,

14:07.300 --> 14:08.633
I'm taking her out
for a nice dinner.

14:08.667 --> 14:11.767
- Saying goodbye.
- Bru, Bru, Bruno!

14:12.000 --> 14:13.367
You the man, brother man.

14:13.400 --> 14:15.166
Oh-ho-ho!
You guys are all right.

14:15.200 --> 14:16.700
Nic--oh, other hand.

14:16.700 --> 14:18.433
[laughter]
Nico...

14:18.433 --> 14:20.166
- Good luck to you, man.
- Take care, buddy...

14:20.200 --> 14:22.700
- Yeah, Thank you.
- And finish hard!

14:22.734 --> 14:24.700
- Yeah, for sure.
- We will.

14:24.700 --> 14:27.767
- Away!

14:28.000 --> 14:29.667
- [imitates explosion]
- Ah!

14:29.700 --> 14:31.233
See you guys.
- Good luck.

14:31.266 --> 14:33.300
- See you, man.
- One more hug.

14:33.333 --> 14:34.567
- I'm gonna miss you, Baker.

14:34.600 --> 14:36.333
- Aw. [laughs] Bye.

14:36.367 --> 14:37.734
- We'll see you soon, Baker.

14:37.767 --> 14:39.333
I feel like
I'm leaving this boat

14:39.367 --> 14:41.200
in a much better place
than I came.

14:41.233 --> 14:44.333
The deck team has graduated
to where they need to be,

14:44.333 --> 14:46.600
and I think Nico could be
an excellent bosun.

14:46.633 --> 14:49.133
- Ciao. [screams]
- Whoa!

14:49.166 --> 14:50.700
- But I think
he needs to drop his ego,

14:50.734 --> 14:53.066
stop being such a child.

14:53.066 --> 14:54.300
He's still got
a long way to go.

14:54.333 --> 14:57.200
- Bye.

14:57.200 --> 15:00.200
[upbeat music]

15:00.200 --> 15:02.600
♪ ♪

15:02.600 --> 15:04.433
- Kate, Matt, Nico,

15:04.467 --> 15:06.000
I need you guys
in the crew mess now.

15:06.033 --> 15:07.333
- Copy.

15:07.367 --> 15:09.066
♪ ♪

15:09.100 --> 15:12.066
- [mumbles]

15:12.066 --> 15:13.467
- Number eight.

15:13.467 --> 15:16.200
Shelly Snoddy.
She's our primary.

15:16.233 --> 15:18.333
She's an attorney
for her family business.

15:18.367 --> 15:21.166
We have eight women.
The ultimate girls' trip.

15:21.200 --> 15:25.333
Dislikes: not specified.
I don't see anything crazy.

15:25.367 --> 15:27.467
Amenities: gourmet meals
from the chief.

15:27.500 --> 15:29.300
That would be you.
- Excellent.

15:29.333 --> 15:31.100
- It's very embarrassing
to have a charter guest

15:31.100 --> 15:32.500
shred your chef.

15:32.533 --> 15:34.433
This is the second time
this season.

15:34.467 --> 15:36.300
- It was really
pretty flawless. I mean--

15:36.333 --> 15:38.033
- Except for the
chocolate ice cream,

15:38.066 --> 15:40.033
vanilla ice cream issue
we had the first night.

15:40.066 --> 15:42.200
- Our bar is up here.
If you're not there,

15:42.233 --> 15:44.567
you're probably not
the right person for the job.

15:44.600 --> 15:47.333
They're requesting
a Caribbean carnival theme,

15:47.367 --> 15:50.467
surf and turf dinner party
with entertainment and games.

15:50.500 --> 15:51.767
- That's really cool.

15:52.000 --> 15:53.600
- We're gonna have
a new deckhand.

15:53.633 --> 15:55.700
We should be able
to provide these ladies

15:55.734 --> 15:58.233
with everything they need.
- Cool.

15:58.266 --> 16:00.233
- Just to have another set
of hands come on board is good,

16:00.266 --> 16:01.667
but it'd be nice
to have a deckhand

16:01.667 --> 16:04.266
that actually knows
what yachting is,

16:04.300 --> 16:07.133
maybe what a shammy is, rather
than someone that's green.

16:07.133 --> 16:08.767
- That's a wrap.

16:09.000 --> 16:11.767
[electronic music]

16:12.000 --> 16:14.600
♪ ♪

16:14.633 --> 16:17.600
- Nico, lead.
- Go ahead, Cap.

16:17.633 --> 16:20.600
- Can I get you to
the starboard side gangplank.

16:20.633 --> 16:21.734
- Absolutely, Captain.

16:21.767 --> 16:24.233
- Hello.
- Hi, Nico.

16:24.266 --> 16:26.066
- Let me grab your bags
for you, huh?

16:26.100 --> 16:27.266
- Thank you so much.
- Hi, baby.

16:27.300 --> 16:28.667
- Hi, baby.
How are you?

16:28.700 --> 16:32.066
- I'm great.
It's good to see you.

16:32.100 --> 16:34.266
This season has been
just extremely trying.

16:34.300 --> 16:37.567
Green deckhands,
green interior crew,

16:37.567 --> 16:39.433
crappy weather.

16:39.433 --> 16:42.233
- This is really nice.
- To have Mary Anne come out

16:42.266 --> 16:45.233
and give me just a little bit
of respite from the grind

16:45.266 --> 16:47.500
is really a pleasure.

16:47.533 --> 16:51.367
I'm glad you came.
- I'm excited.

16:51.400 --> 16:53.200
- Hey.
- Hi.

16:55.700 --> 16:57.667
- I woke up first today.
I'm tired.

16:57.700 --> 17:00.033
It seems like we don't hustle
enough to get the work done.

17:00.066 --> 17:02.100
The sooner we get the work
done, the sooner we take a nap.

17:02.133 --> 17:04.033
- I totally think Kate's
failing me as a boss,

17:04.033 --> 17:05.300
as a mentor.

17:05.300 --> 17:07.033
You know, I looked up to her.

17:07.066 --> 17:08.533
Instead, she's abused me,

17:08.567 --> 17:10.667
played mind games with me,
emotionally.

17:10.700 --> 17:13.367
I have no respect for her.
- I put a list in Sky Lounge.

17:13.400 --> 17:15.300
after you take the trash out,
you can come look at it.

17:15.333 --> 17:17.433
- If you take a hard left...
- Hi. You look amazing.

17:17.433 --> 17:19.033
- Hi. Thank you.

17:19.066 --> 17:20.600
When did you get in?
- Just now.

17:20.633 --> 17:23.333
- I love Captain Lee
and Mary Anne as a couple.

17:23.333 --> 17:25.600
They're like
high school sweethearts.

17:25.600 --> 17:27.600
Captain Lee and I talk on the
phone at least once a week,

17:27.600 --> 17:29.400
and he always tells me
about four minutes

17:29.433 --> 17:30.667
into the conversation that
I'm on speakerphone

17:30.700 --> 17:32.333
with Mary Anne, and I'm like,

17:32.367 --> 17:35.166
"I know. Hi, Mary Anne."
It's cute.

17:35.200 --> 17:38.700
Oh, you two young lovebirds.
[chuckles]

17:38.734 --> 17:42.200
- Man, she's in a great mood.
I f---ing love my boss.

17:42.200 --> 17:43.400
- You look amazing.
Have you been working out?

17:43.433 --> 17:44.700
- She does look good,
doesn't she?

17:44.734 --> 17:46.166
- She looks good.
- You cannot eat.

17:46.200 --> 17:48.533
You cannot sleep.
You will work.

17:50.033 --> 17:52.400
♪ ♪

17:52.433 --> 17:55.000
- Holy sh--.

17:55.033 --> 17:56.400
- Well, look who it is.

18:00.100 --> 18:00.467
[slow electronic music]

18:03.500 --> 18:05.500
- So, if you want,
you can just pack the bag,

18:05.533 --> 18:07.100
and I can just carry
this tonight,

18:07.100 --> 18:08.600
rather than coming
back to the boat,

18:08.633 --> 18:10.700
and we can just go
straight to the hotel.

18:10.734 --> 18:12.467
I'm excited just to get off the
boat, spend some time with Bri.

18:12.500 --> 18:14.200
We'll just kind of
go to the hotel.

18:14.233 --> 18:16.100
- That sounds so good.

18:16.100 --> 18:17.734
- And just get some tension
off my shoulders.

18:17.767 --> 18:19.767
It's been a high-stress
situation all season.

18:19.767 --> 18:21.467
- Cool, cool.
- All right.

18:21.500 --> 18:24.467
[fast-paced
instrumental music]

18:24.500 --> 18:26.367
♪ ♪

18:26.400 --> 18:27.700
- I went to the zoo once,

18:27.734 --> 18:29.200
and an elephant threw up
all over me.

18:29.233 --> 18:30.633
All I heard was just
bowel movements,

18:30.667 --> 18:32.500
and then suddenly, "Woosh!"
- [groans]

18:32.500 --> 18:35.033
[laughs]
- You look great, sweetie.

18:35.066 --> 18:37.333
- All right, shall we?
- We shall.

18:37.367 --> 18:39.633
- Here we go. Ready?
- All right.

18:39.633 --> 18:42.133
- Good evening.
- Oh, it's so peaceful.

18:42.133 --> 18:44.100
[indistinct chatter]

18:44.133 --> 18:45.734
- I'll do an espresso
martini, please.

18:45.767 --> 18:47.266
- Espresso martini.

18:47.300 --> 18:48.533
- I would like
the same, please. Thanks.

18:48.533 --> 18:50.233
- Two more.
- Two more?

18:50.266 --> 18:51.767
- Oui, oui.
- How's your arm, buddy?

18:52.000 --> 18:54.000
- Feels a lot better.
- Don't push it. Just...

18:54.033 --> 18:56.000
- Yeah. Thank you.
- This is really nice

18:56.000 --> 18:57.100
being right on the water,
isn't it?

18:57.133 --> 18:58.533
- Oh, it's great.

18:58.567 --> 19:00.133
- Captain,
how did you guys meet?

19:00.166 --> 19:01.734
I wanna know.
- We met--

19:01.767 --> 19:04.500
- The story of how we met--
here we go again.

19:04.533 --> 19:06.200
- My girlfriends knew him.

19:06.233 --> 19:07.767
We all went out one night,
and I met Lee,

19:08.000 --> 19:10.066
and he doesn't remember
meeting me. [laughs]

19:10.100 --> 19:12.467
I made such a good impression.

19:12.500 --> 19:14.266
- How can you
hold me responsible

19:14.266 --> 19:16.734
for something I don't remember?
That's not fair.

19:16.767 --> 19:18.500
- Well, then we met again,
about maybe a month later,

19:18.533 --> 19:20.200
and he loved me.

19:20.233 --> 19:21.266
- And after the second time,
that was it.

19:21.300 --> 19:23.100
- Aw.
- Yeah.

19:23.133 --> 19:24.700
- That's awesome.
- Cheers to Mary Anne visiting.

19:24.700 --> 19:26.233
- Yes. Thank you for visiting.
- So good to see

19:26.266 --> 19:27.567
the other half of Captain Lee.

19:27.600 --> 19:29.100
Cheers.
- The best half.

19:29.133 --> 19:30.667
[laughter]

19:30.700 --> 19:32.533
We've been married 42 years,

19:32.567 --> 19:34.767
and after putting up
with me and five kids,

19:35.000 --> 19:36.533
she has the patience
of a saint,

19:36.567 --> 19:38.166
and I happen to be
one of those guys

19:38.166 --> 19:39.567
who got to marry
their best friend.

19:39.567 --> 19:41.567
- We'll play musical chairs.
- Hi.

19:41.600 --> 19:44.433
- Oh. Thank you so much.
- Oh, my goodness.

19:44.467 --> 19:46.633
- I appreciate you having us
for dinner and everything.

19:46.667 --> 19:48.433
Your wife is amazing.

19:48.433 --> 19:50.367
- She's the best.
- She's cool.

19:50.400 --> 19:52.033
She's just proud to,
like, be with you.

19:52.066 --> 19:53.433
It's nice to actually see that.
- Yeah.

19:53.433 --> 19:55.667
- For a relationship
to last a long time,

19:55.700 --> 19:57.133
you have to work at it.

19:57.166 --> 19:59.500
I care more about
making her happy

19:59.533 --> 20:01.400
than what I want for myself.

20:01.433 --> 20:03.700
If she's got a smile
on her face, my day's complete.

20:03.700 --> 20:05.300
I'm done.

20:05.300 --> 20:06.600
- You see a whole
'nother side of Lee

20:06.633 --> 20:08.200
when he's around Mary Anne.

20:08.233 --> 20:09.700
He's suddenly
this big teddy bear.

20:09.734 --> 20:12.033
- I'm a very fortunate man.
- You are.

20:12.066 --> 20:13.133
- I know it.

20:13.166 --> 20:15.000
[gentle guitar music]

20:15.033 --> 20:16.467
- All right, Cap.

20:16.500 --> 20:19.066
I appreciate you.
Thanks for having us.

20:19.066 --> 20:21.333
- Good night, Captain.
- I'll see you guys later.

20:21.333 --> 20:23.600
- Au revoir. Make it good.
- Are they an item?

20:23.600 --> 20:26.066
- I think it's official.
I think he's made it official.

20:26.100 --> 20:28.133
- He's such a romantic.
- Captain?

20:28.166 --> 20:29.467
- Yeah.
- Oh, is he giving you advice?

20:29.467 --> 20:31.400
[giggles]
- Oh, my God.

20:31.433 --> 20:33.166
It's nice to see a functional
relationship in yachting.

20:33.200 --> 20:37.600
You don't see that often,
especially from captains.

20:37.600 --> 20:40.066
- So, Lee, what do you think
about us losing EJ?

20:40.100 --> 20:42.033
- I wasn't happy to see him go.

20:42.066 --> 20:43.533
You never have to
worry about him

20:43.567 --> 20:45.600
in the effort department, so...

20:45.633 --> 20:48.066
- When you're in a critical
position, to have an employee

20:48.100 --> 20:50.066
that brings
that much to the table,

20:50.100 --> 20:51.500
you can't replicate that.

20:51.533 --> 20:54.233
That's, um--it's a--

20:54.266 --> 20:56.367
a delicacy for sure.

20:56.400 --> 21:00.066
- Mmm, delicacy.
- Well, here's to EJ.

21:00.100 --> 21:02.734
Cheers.
Salud, salud.

21:02.767 --> 21:04.367
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

21:04.367 --> 21:07.233
- Here we are.

21:07.266 --> 21:09.367
- I'm gonna call it a night.
- Yeah, let's do it.

21:09.400 --> 21:11.600
- It was great meeting you.
- Thank you, Captain.

21:11.633 --> 21:13.767
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

21:13.767 --> 21:15.000
- [sighs]

21:18.400 --> 21:20.367
♪ ♪

21:20.400 --> 21:23.100
- All in all, I'd say
dinner was a huge success.

21:23.133 --> 21:24.633
Bruno stayed quiet,

21:24.667 --> 21:26.367
Matt didn't get
blackout drunk,

21:26.367 --> 21:28.233
Jen didn't cause
too much of a scene,

21:28.266 --> 21:30.200
and Nico's about to get lucky
with Bri in a hotel room.

21:30.233 --> 21:31.600
- Oh, my God,
we're holding hands.

21:31.633 --> 21:33.266
It's so official.

21:33.266 --> 21:35.467
[giggles]
I want my dessert.

21:35.500 --> 21:37.100
[moans]

21:37.133 --> 21:40.667
♪ ♪

21:40.700 --> 21:43.667
[upbeat music]

21:43.700 --> 21:45.400
♪ ♪

21:45.400 --> 21:46.533
- Did you have fun?
- [laughs]

21:46.533 --> 21:48.233
- That's nice. Really nice.

21:48.266 --> 21:49.367
- [groans]

21:49.400 --> 21:53.633
♪ ♪

21:53.667 --> 21:55.233
[chuckles]

21:55.266 --> 21:56.667
- Are you gonna keep this?
- Yeah.

21:56.700 --> 21:58.367
- Is this what you wore
on your head?

21:58.400 --> 22:00.100
- No, that's not
what I wore on my head.

22:00.133 --> 22:02.367
- What'd you wear?
- Kate made something up.

22:02.400 --> 22:05.400
I'm Don Ho's brother, Ass.
[laughter]

22:05.433 --> 22:07.000
You can take that
home with you,

22:07.033 --> 22:09.000
just so I don't forget it.
- I can?

22:09.033 --> 22:10.400
- Sure.
- Well, what'd you think?

22:10.400 --> 22:12.166
You think we'll get
a new decky?

22:12.166 --> 22:14.667
- It's so weird,
people leaving, people coming.

22:14.700 --> 22:16.433
- Yeah, I thought you were just
gonna have a sip of my coffee.

22:16.433 --> 22:19.133
- Can I have the last one?
[laughs]

22:19.166 --> 22:23.233
Yes, hello. I saw your web site
about acrobatics on yachts.

22:23.266 --> 22:25.400
I was wondering
if you'd be available.

22:25.433 --> 22:27.133
Perfect.
Eighth charter is starting,

22:27.166 --> 22:29.133
and we're having
a Carnival-themed party,

22:29.166 --> 22:32.233
and I am excited, because
I've never done one before,

22:32.266 --> 22:33.667
which kind of confused me.

22:33.700 --> 22:35.500
How had I never done
a Carnival-theme?

22:35.533 --> 22:37.033
I've been in the Caribbean,
like, a million seasons.

22:37.066 --> 22:39.433
Hello?
All right. Thank you. Bye.

22:39.433 --> 22:42.133
- Let's go.

22:42.166 --> 22:44.300
My wife and I don't get to
communicate all that much

22:44.300 --> 22:45.700
while I'm out at sea,

22:45.734 --> 22:47.700
so saying good-bye
is never easy.

22:47.734 --> 22:49.700
Nico, pick up, please.
- Go ahead.

22:49.700 --> 22:51.700
- Can you get Mary Anne's bags
out of the master, please?

22:51.734 --> 22:54.467
- Absolutely. On my way.
- Thank you.

22:54.500 --> 22:56.200
The finish line is in sight,

22:56.233 --> 22:57.533
and it just works out
really well.

22:57.567 --> 22:59.567
It's a really nice treat.

22:59.600 --> 23:01.700
- Love you.
- Nico, take her down there.

23:01.734 --> 23:04.567
- Can I ride in that too?
- Yeah, absolutely. Get in.

23:04.600 --> 23:07.033
[both laugh]

23:07.066 --> 23:08.066
- [sighs]

23:08.100 --> 23:11.200
♪ ♪

23:11.233 --> 23:13.333
- [whistling]

23:13.367 --> 23:15.433
- I'm excited
the weather cleared out.

23:15.467 --> 23:17.567
- You know, and we should be
good for the rest of this week.

23:17.600 --> 23:19.700
- Good way to end the season.
- You're back in charge.

23:19.734 --> 23:21.300
- Yeah.
- Two more charters.

23:21.333 --> 23:23.600
Finish out the rest
of the season strong.

23:23.600 --> 23:25.300
- Yeah.

23:25.333 --> 23:27.734
- Supposedly a new crew
arriving today.

23:27.734 --> 23:29.734
- It's so crazy.

23:29.767 --> 23:31.533
- Fine with me to have
an extra hand on deck.

23:31.567 --> 23:33.333
[chuckles]

23:33.333 --> 23:34.767
unless it was, like,
someone completely green,

23:34.767 --> 23:37.567
and then that
might be a setback.

23:37.600 --> 23:40.433
- Holy sh--.

