will be not at the same level.

38:16.700 --> 38:18.600
He's been very lucky
many times.

38:18.633 --> 38:21.467
- I want him to do it.
I don't want Bruno to do it.

38:21.500 --> 38:24.333
"No, you're putting too much
lettuce on that, Matt."

38:24.367 --> 38:28.000
Really? Maybe we just pull
Bruno out of the galley.

38:28.033 --> 38:30.266
- I agree that Bruno has spent
too much time in the galley,

38:30.266 --> 38:32.000
but unfortunately,
I think that

38:32.033 --> 38:33.633
Matt has come
to depend on Bruno

38:33.667 --> 38:36.133
so much at this point
that pulling Bruno away

38:36.166 --> 38:38.000
could actually make
the situation worse.

38:38.033 --> 38:39.633
- Nico, Lee.
- Go ahead, Cap.

38:39.667 --> 38:42.133
- To the wheelhouse.
- On my way.

38:42.133 --> 38:44.533
[solemn music]

38:44.567 --> 38:47.400
- Kate and I were just having
a conversation about Matt.

38:47.400 --> 38:49.200
I don't think
Bruno's helping him;

38:49.233 --> 38:50.667
I think he's hindering him.

38:50.700 --> 38:54.367
So, tomorrow, I want
Bruno doing deckhand sh--.

38:54.400 --> 38:56.133
I need Matt to stand
on his own two feet

38:56.166 --> 38:57.667
and show me
some creative ability.

38:57.700 --> 39:00.433
Matt seems to have
this unknown fear

39:00.467 --> 39:02.500
of putting himself out there,

39:02.533 --> 39:04.233
and that's not what people
wanna see when they come

39:04.266 --> 39:05.633
on board a five-start yacht.

39:05.667 --> 39:07.567
They wanna see
five-star food.

39:07.567 --> 39:10.166
So I'm hoping that taking
Bruno out of the galley

39:10.200 --> 39:12.266
will maybe piss him off
to the point where he goes,

39:12.300 --> 39:14.033
"I'll show
that son of a bitch."

39:14.033 --> 39:16.300
This charter and the next one
are really important.

39:16.333 --> 39:18.300
♪ ♪

39:18.333 --> 39:21.300
[electronic music]

39:21.333 --> 39:28.367
♪ ♪

39:39.066 --> 39:41.200
- Guys, get over here.
Let's get the hook off.

39:41.200 --> 39:42.633
- Copy.

39:44.600 --> 39:47.200
- Steady and just hold.
- Copy that.

39:49.600 --> 39:51.433
- Do you mind if I put
some pastries out,

39:51.467 --> 39:53.066
or do you like to do that?

39:53.066 --> 39:54.700
- Well, we're doing
a [inaudible]--

39:54.734 --> 39:58.667
- This is what my boss
told me to do, so...

39:58.700 --> 40:00.700
- Just hear me out, Jen?
- I will.

40:00.734 --> 40:02.700
I have Captain telling me one
thing, Kate tells me another.

40:02.734 --> 40:04.066
I'm just always caught
in the middle.

40:04.066 --> 40:05.567
- We're gonna do chocolate.

40:05.600 --> 40:07.066
These ones are going
on the picnic today.

40:07.066 --> 40:08.200
- Got it.
- And then a couple of

40:08.233 --> 40:09.600
these guys will be perfect.

40:09.600 --> 40:11.333
- Thank you.
- How are you doing?

40:11.333 --> 40:13.133
- It took me a while
to f---ing figure it out,

40:13.166 --> 40:15.166
and I don't even think
it's right still, but--

40:15.200 --> 40:17.200
- I guess I'm just still grumpy
from your deplorable thing

40:17.233 --> 40:19.300
you said to me last night.

40:19.333 --> 40:22.433
- I feel like you're miserable.
I want you to not be miserable.

40:22.467 --> 40:24.300
Okay, well, it is what
it is at this point.

40:24.333 --> 40:25.767
- Well, for future reference,

40:26.000 --> 40:27.467
you should never call
your boss miserable.

40:27.500 --> 40:29.233
- It had nothing to do
with the boss.

40:29.233 --> 40:30.734
If my boss implies that
I'm a whore, then...

40:30.767 --> 40:32.633
- No, I didn't.
You said I was a whore.

40:32.633 --> 40:34.734
- I'm going to stand up
for myself and my daughter...

40:34.767 --> 40:36.633
- You said I was a whore.
- That's all there is to it.

40:36.667 --> 40:38.166
I will get fired for standing
up for the fact that...

40:38.200 --> 40:39.500
- I never said
you were a whore.

40:39.533 --> 40:41.200
- I have to stick up
for my daughter.

40:41.233 --> 40:42.333
- Jen and Kate. What's up?
- Nothing.

40:42.367 --> 40:44.433
They're just cat-fighting.

40:44.467 --> 40:46.233
- I'm gonna leave it at that.
I mean, we're going in circles.

40:46.233 --> 40:49.500
Kate has pushed me
to my boiling point.

40:49.533 --> 40:51.100
For her to spin this on me

40:51.133 --> 40:53.100
like I'm the one
that said something awful

40:53.133 --> 40:56.200
about her being miserable--
are you kidding me?

40:56.233 --> 40:59.000
So the best thing
that I can do is walk away.

40:59.033 --> 41:01.633
- Morning. Thank you so much.
- You are most welcome,

41:01.667 --> 41:03.133
and I got the sugar
right over here.

41:03.133 --> 41:05.400
I'll grab it for you.

41:05.433 --> 41:08.400
- Words from above.
- Oh, the captain?

41:08.433 --> 41:12.266
- Yeah. He wants to see more
of, like, Matt being the chef

41:12.266 --> 41:14.633
